# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Model configuration secrets.  Copy this file to  secrets/secrets.env  and edit.
#   secrets/secrets.env is GITIGNORED — your keys never get committed.
#
# The CLIs (review/match/coach/generate/linkedin) and the web app load this file
# automatically.  Values already set in your shell environment always win over
# this file.  Pick ONE of the two setups below.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# ===== Option A: LOCAL model (Ollama / llama.cpp on your machine) ============
# No API key needed for an open local endpoint.
LLM_BASE_URL=http://localhost:11434/v1
LLM_MODEL=llama3.1:8b
# LLM_API_KEY=            # leave empty for a local, unsecured endpoint

# ===== Option B: HOSTED llama server over the web ===========================
# Comment out Option A above and use these instead.  `LLAMA_SERVER_URL` and
# `API_KEY` are friendly aliases — the loader maps them to LLM_BASE_URL /
# LLM_API_KEY for you.
#
# LLAMA_SERVER_URL=https://your-llama-server.example.com/v1
# API_KEY=your-secret-bearer-token          # matches the server's --api-key
# LLAMA_MODEL=local                          # single-model llama-server ignores this

# ===== Optional request tuning (either setup) ===============================
# LLM_TIMEOUT_MS=120000     # raise for slow CPU / reasoning models over the web
# LLM_MAX_TOKENS=2048
# LLM_SEED=0

# ===== Storage ==============================================================
# DATA_DIR=.data            # where the version snapshot store lives
